Haven't been here in quite some time, mostly due to Covid. They've changed up the place some. Most genres have changed location and they still want masks worn. Couldn't find the Science fiction shelves, so satisfied my curiosity with the fantasy section. Also noticed there isn't a lot of choice in religious writers section. There are a few prominent religious authors that are conspicuously absent. I did find 3 books that were of interest, however. I'm not sure if the scarcity of choice is because of online competition or a poor choice of the buyers for the store/chain. I would like to give my business to the brick and mortar, because I love looking through the different section and being surprised by something I wouldn't have noticed while online. The browsing and the feel and smell of tangible books is something I love, but get to experience way to infrequently. I'd recommend this store that is trying to hold it together against the odds. They also have diversified their  stock. Worth a stop in to get a feel for the past and possibly picking up something for quite times.
